I'm going to no-vote. I'll second (sixth?) the opinion that the idea doesn't have a huge amount going for it, for all the reasons mentioned above. Regarding the science, I'm of two minds about it. (Pun accidental.)  is a very rare but observed complication of brain injury, so it's not like you're plucking this phenomenon totally out of the air. Additionally, you've deployed a really pleasing amount of medical concepts and terminology to describe it - seriously, well done. It does, however, seem to me that you're shoehorning in your personal experiences and biases about left vs. right brains. The actual neurology of creativity is not well understood.

If you do really want to start getting technical about this idea - which I would actively encourage - you can cover your ass pretty easily. There are so many bits of the brain associated with 

